In MSTest v4, `[ExpectedException]` was removed. The replacement is **`Assert.ThrowsExactly<TException>()`** (inline in the test body):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}

[TestMethod]
public void Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => Process());
}
```

For **async** methods, use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<TException>(...)`.

**Benefits over `[ExpectedException]`:**
- Pinpoints *which line* should throw (no false passes if an earlier line throws)
- Returns the exception object so you can assert on `.Message`, `.ParamName`, etc.

